    </lead_sponsor>
  </sponsors>
  <source>NEMA Research, Inc.</source>
  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Using a retrospective analysis of a large commercial claims database and a Medicare database,
      the investigators evaluated DDEs that have the potential to cause DDIs among chronic low back
      pain (cLBP) patients on long-term opioid analgesia, which metabolizes through the CYP450
      enzyme system, concomitant with other CYP450-metabolized drug(s).
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
